    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      48.96,
      180.65,
      67.62
    ],
    "text": "Social Entrepreneurs",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      79.24,
      453.01,
      109.01
    ],
    "text": "Social entrepreneurs are those who submit or show creative solutions for social problems.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      121.24,
      453.02,
      165.01
    ],
    "text": "Today, the society faces a lot of problems. Spread of epidemic diseases, problems of nutrition, problems of illiteracy, use of drugs, and poverty are some of them. People who endeavour to solve these problems creatively are known as social entrepreneurs.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      176.94,
      453.01,
      291.04
    ],
    "text": "Example :- Grameen loan system Introduction of activities related to eradication of epidemic diseases. Social entrepreneurs attempt to transform the society by proposing various solutions to these social issues. These can be seen implemented provincially, nationally and internationally. There are number of world famous entrepreneurs.",
    "fonts": [
      "FMAbhaya",
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldItal",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      302.97,
      397.64,
      361.05
    ],
    "text": "Example :- Mahatma Gandhi, Marie Curie, Prof. Mohomad Yoonus. Nationally, we have a number of popular social entrepreneurs.",
    "fonts": [
      "FMAbhaya",
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldItal",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      372.97,
      245.43,
      403.05
    ],
    "text": "Example :- Dr. C.W.W. Kannangara",
    "fonts": [
      "FMAbhaya",
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldItal",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      412.96,
      279.05,
      431.62
    ],
    "text": "Internal (institutional) Entrepreneurs",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      14.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      443.24,
      453.02,
      487.01
    ],
    "text": "A recent attention has been focused on the type of people called internal entrepreneurs. These entrepreneurs can be seen among the existing employees in the business.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      499.24,
      453.01,
      543.02
    ],
    "text": "Internal entrepreneurs are those who hold top level jobs within the business with entrepreneurial skills. These people make changes on their own as examples to others.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 9,
    "bbox": [
      54.0,
      552.95,
      453.06,
      597.03
    ],
    "text": "Example :- Heads of government institutions who have won awards for quality. Principals of schools who have won awards for productivity.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldItal",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
